    "infrastructure": {
      "rounds": [
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`Path::is_file()` here treats any metadata/stat failure or non-regular `plan.md` as if the file were simply absent, so a dangling symlink, directory named `plan.md`, or permission error now silently skips the freshness check instead of failing closed. That regresses the previous I/O error path and can let corrupted tracks bypass `validate_track_snapshots`.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/render.rs",
              "line": 602,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:60600b5f65d0c47f7dae14792aaf6cb7af0e25bf1c78ffe670555a19512d1a65",
          "at": "2026-04-23T02:35:24Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`plan_path.is_file()` treats unreadable or broken `plan.md` paths the same as a missing file, so validation will now silently skip tracks whose plan exists but cannot be accessed instead of surfacing the filesystem error or an out-of-sync state. The Phase 0 exception should only cover the file being absent.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/render.rs",
              "line": 602,
              "category": "error handling"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:60600b5f65d0c47f7dae14792aaf6cb7af0e25bf1c78ffe670555a19512d1a65",
          "at": "2026-04-23T02:36:13Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "This guard skips validation for any non-regular `plan.md`, not just a missing file. A directory, FIFO, or other malformed path named `plan.md` will now be treated as absent and bypass the freshness check instead of surfacing an error, which can let corrupted tracks pass validation.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/render.rs",
              "line": 605,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:c7f312d61d08e630adf8f7e7b6b30cb20e92bdb5d08aaff429ade5714bcd47f6",
          "at": "2026-04-23T02:41:33Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The new `NotFound => continue` path skips validation for every v5 snapshot with a missing `plan.md`, so a later-phase track whose rendered plan was deleted or never regenerated now passes `validate_track_snapshots` instead of failing. This only makes sense for the intended Phase 0 case when the plan artifact is not supposed to exist yet; as written, the check fails open for any v5 track lacking `plan.md`.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/render.rs",
              "line": 607,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:58dc0ebd4421a82f4352477531ee19e7491be32ff9b337c66828412d05041828",
          "at": "2026-04-23T02:43:41Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`impl_plan_path.is_file()` silently folds permission errors, broken symlinks, and other metadata failures into “absent”, so a v5 snapshot with no `plan.md` can now pass validation even when `impl-plan.json` is present but inaccessible/corrupted. That makes the new Phase 0 escape hatch fail open for later-phase tracks; it should propagate filesystem errors instead of treating every non-regular path as missing.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/render.rs",
              "line": 613,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:94db522d70a18570efa92318c024f498d6cdda7c55febf79a4bc828a311a87e2",
          "at": "2026-04-23T02:46:13Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The new missing-plan guard only skips validation when `impl-plan.json` is also absent. That narrows the intended Phase 0 compatibility too far: any v5 track where `plan.md` has not been rendered yet but `impl-plan.json` is already present will now fail with `OutOfSync`, even though the requested behavior was to tolerate a missing `plan.md` and just skip the content check.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/track/render.rs",
              "line": 607,
              "category": "correctness"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:b65abb4e9338035a71142514d1bbdcf122249c896e9f59d24fcc2ae89ea99122",
          "at": "2026-04-23T02:49:19Z"
