              "message": "`SpecRequirement::signal()` still documents the old ADR-first rule, saying non-empty `adr_refs[]` returns Blue and only ADR-empty informal grounds return Yellow. The implementation now delegates to `evaluate_requirement_signal`, where informal grounds take priority even when ADR refs are present, so the public API rustdoc advertises the wrong domain rule for callers of this method.",
