          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The new rule says universal coding principles such as no-panics must be cited only in top-level `related_conventions[]` and dropped from per-element entries, but the immediately preceding existing guidance still tells the agent to encode “No panics in library code” into per-element `constraints[]` when applicable. That leaves the spec-designer with contradictory placement instructions, so it can still make the exact no-panics placement decision this change is intended to eliminate.",
